Narrative:
Jose Buttler of Rajasthan Royals  inched closer to Virat Kohli's record of scoring four hundreds in a single IPL season. 

The Indian batter was the top run-scorer of the 2016 IPL edition, where he amassed 973 runs from 16 matches, which included four centuries and seven half-centuries.
Title: Jose Butler can surpass Virat Kohli's record ⏺️
